{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"654df67f-83ca-449f-9bac-57d787a22dbe","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_OKohgNeINJrj3GXCmueR4q","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0e8eb816dfd1429aa7be4f7aefe61802/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-0e8eb816dfd1429aa7be4f7aefe61802/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f885eba2-a30a-4327-96b5-4d56ce8baba0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed earlier in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />   <!-- Listed first -->\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />     <!-- Listed second -->\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />    <!-- Listed third -->\n```\n\nBut `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. Since `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, the compiler hasn't seen `Domain` yet when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\n\nThe fix is straightforward: reorder the files so `Domain.fs` compiles first since it has no dependencies, then `Services.fs` which depends on it, and finally `Program.fs` which needs both.","outputTokens":502,"requestId":"73D2:15979F:158B935:1815969:6A051DAB"},"id":"95f33f5a-2383-479d-8a51-2b3bd4447145","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:20.895Z","parentId":"d51eae45-3a7a-46cb-8119-62ab47d31c52"}
